# =============================================================================
# VectorForge Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
# ---------------------
# 1. Copy this file to a new file named ".env" (without quotes)
#    Command: cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Open the new .env file and replace the placeholder values below
#
# 3. Save the file and restart your dev server (npm run dev)
#
# For detailed instructions, see: docs/ENVIRONMENT_SETUP.md
#
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Azure AI Configuration
# =============================================================================
# You need ALL THREE of these values for AI features to work!
#
# WHERE TO FIND THESE:
# 1. Go to https://portal.azure.com
# 2. Search for "Azure OpenAI" and click your resource
# 3. Click "Keys and Endpoint" in the left sidebar
# 4. Copy the Endpoint URL and one of the API keys
# 5. For deployment name, go to "Model deployments" to see what you named it

# Your Azure OpenAI endpoint URL (copy from Azure Portal > Keys and Endpoint)
# Example: https://my-resource.openai.azure.com/
AZURE_AI_ENDPOINT=PASTE_YOUR_ENDPOINT_HERE

# Your Azure API key (copy from Azure Portal > Keys and Endpoint > KEY 1 or KEY 2)
# Example: xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
AZURE_SECRET_KEY=PASTE_YOUR_API_KEY_HERE

# The name of your deployed model (whatever you named it when you deployed)
# Example: gpt-4o
AZURE_AI_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=PASTE_YOUR_DEPLOYMENT_NAME_HERE

# =============================================================================
# ALTERNATIVE: OpenAI Configuration (if not using Azure)
# =============================================================================
# Uncomment the line below and add your OpenAI API key
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Skip Azure Validation (for builds without AI features)
# =============================================================================
# Set this to true if you want to build without configuring Azure AI.
# AI features will be disabled at runtime.
#
# SKIP_AZURE_VALIDATION=true

# =============================================================================
# COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID:
# =============================================================================
# ❌ Don't add spaces around the = sign
# ❌ Don't add quotes around values
# ❌ Don't name the file .env.txt or env (it must be exactly .env)
# ❌ Don't forget to restart the server after changes
# ❌ Don't put this file in a subfolder (it goes in the project root)
# =============================================================================
